Types of variable with respect to their scope/reach/frames.

There are three types of variables :
    1)Local variables
    2) instance variables
    3) static variable


  Local variable:
    A Variable that is created inside a main method loop switch case or any block of code withing {} is called local variable.

    for(int i=0 ; i<3;i++){

    i is local variable
    }


instant variable

instance var that is declared outside of block of code but inside a class

Static Variable :

if an instance variable has a keyword static is called a static vairable.